<h2> HOLLY JOLLY CHRISMAS </h2>

<h2 id="one-4-chord-progression-for-the-entire-song">One 4-chord progression for the entire song!</h2>

<p>This entire song uses a single 4-chord progression, repeating over and over. This makes things super simple to memorize, since you donâ€™t need to remember something different for the verse vs. chorus vs. intro, etc. A choice youâ€™ll have to make is whether or not you use a capo. If you donâ€™t use a capo, youâ€™ll need to play one barre chord (B minor). You could use a capo on the 2nd or 7th fret â€“ the latter allowing you to play the progression using no capo. This can be handy if you donâ€™t know barre chords yet.</p>

<p>Chord progression used if you use <em>no capo</em>:</p>

